{"id":"xpoinittest-d048e8","type":"COMMENT","payload":{"id":"cmt-91c4ff91-76bf-42c5-b9ed-9b23ac19fe88","text":"## Summary\n\n- Created `src/game/collision.ts` — `isValidPosition()` checks bounds and locked cell overlap\n- Created `src/game/lock.ts` — `lockPiece()` writes piece cells into a new board array\n- Created `src/hooks/useGameLoop.ts` — manages board/player state, gravity interval (800ms), exposes `moveLeft`, `moveRight`, `hardDrop`\n- Created `src/hooks/useKeyboard.ts` — maps ArrowLeft/Right/Down to game actions, prevents default scroll\n- Updated `src/App.tsx` — wired hooks together\n\n## Rationale\n\nRefs (`playerRef`, `boardRef`) keep the gravity interval closure in sync with current state without restarting the interval on every state change. Hard drop computes the lowest valid Y in a loop then locks immediately.\n\n## Decisions made\n\n- Lock is immediate on landing (no lock delay) — keeps things simple for now.\n- `useKeyboard` uses a stable actions object pattern to avoid re-registering the listener.\n\n## Status\n\nTypeScript compiles clean. Pieces fall, move left/right, hard drop, lock, and new pieces spawn. Ready for review."},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:59:39.166309Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
