{"id":"xpoinittest-094c11","type":"COMMENT","payload":{"id":"cmt-e1c1ed20-0c68-47e1-a3d6-d9a208ea331b","text":"## Summary\n\n- Added `\"gameover\"` to `GameState` in `src/hooks/useGameLoop.ts`\n- `lockAndScore()` checks if the newly spawned piece collides — if so, transitions to gameover\n- Added `playAgain()` action that resets to idle\n- Created `src/components/GameOver.tsx` — overlay with GAME OVER title, final score, 3-char initials input (alphanumeric), Play Again button\n- Styled in `src/App.css` — red neon title, yellow input, reuses start-button style\n\n## Decisions made\n\n- Initials accept letters and numbers (not just letters), per user feedback\n- Input width 120px to fit all 3 characters comfortably\n- Play Again returns to idle (start screen), not directly to playing\n\n## Status\n\nTypeScript compiles clean. Game over detection, overlay, initials input, and restart all working."},"created_at":"2026-07-12T13:58:33.249609Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
