{"id":"xpoinittest-4c8ae5","type":"CREATE","payload":{"dependencies":[{"kind":"depends_on","source_id":"xpoinittest-4c8ae5","target_id":"xpoinittest-f42f98"}],"description":"## What\n\nReplace the current table-based leaderboard with a more graphical retro arcade-style high score display. Classic arcade cabinets showed high scores with:\n\n- Large, stylized text\n- Rank numbers (1st, 2nd, 3rd...)\n- Player initials in a distinct color/font\n- Score with leading zeros or dot separators\n- No dates — just rank, name, score\n- Top score highlighted or in a special color (gold/yellow)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Remove date column from high scores display and storage\n- [ ] Display scores in a retro arcade style (large monospace text, neon colors)\n- [ ] Show rank numbers (1-10) with top 3 in distinct colors (gold, silver, bronze)\n- [ ] Initials and scores in a fixed-width font for alignment\n- [ ] Scores right-aligned with consistent width\n- [ ] Fits the existing neon/1980s aesthetic","estimate":2,"labels":["feature"],"parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","sort_order":"aB","status":"BACKLOG","title":"Retro arcade-style high score display"},"created_at":"2026-07-12T15:53:06.950169Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
